                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kærdo" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kærdo</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kærttu</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>груша</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>pear</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>arsīmæ kærdo ma cæǧd</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не тряси грушу (в компании) с медведем</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>don't shake the pear (in the company) with the bear</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 192</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>arsīmæ kærdo ma cæǧd</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>не тряси грушу (в компании) с медведем</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>don't shake the pear (in the company) with the bear</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 192</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Усвоено из какого-то тюркского языка; ср.<mentioned xml:lang="qwm"><lang/> <w>kärtmä</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1105</biblScope></bibl>). Сюда и <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>körte</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="hu"><w>körtövé</w> <gloss><q>груша</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Встречается и в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/> <w>qjart</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/> <w>qjort</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="aqc"><lang/> <w>xært</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>qor</w></mentioned>. Исходной для осетинского могла быть форма, близкая к венг. %ikörtöve%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 115, III 14</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>I 118–119</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gombocz"/><biblScope>106–107</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"/><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It was acquired from some Turkic language; cf.<mentioned xml:lang="qwm"><lang/> <w>kärtmä</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 1105</biblScope></bibl>). Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/> <w>körte</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="hu"><w>körtövé</w> <gloss><q>pear</q></gloss></mentioned>, . It is attested in Caucasian languages as well: <mentioned xml:lang="dar"><lang/> <w>qjart</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lbe"><lang/> <w>qjort</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="aqc"><lang/> <w>xært</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>qor</w></mentioned>. The initial Ossetic form might have been similar to Hungarian %ikörtöve%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 115, III 14</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>I 118–119</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gombocz"/><biblScope>106–107</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Jacobsohn"/><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>